    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="1421"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1421">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/1761.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1421fn1">The same to the American Ministers to Salvador and
                        Guatemala.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 8.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 31, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: For your information and with reference to Mr.
                    Gunther’s telegram of January 4th to the Department, you are advised that Consul
                    Lee, in whose custody the Legation at San José now is, reported under date of
                    January 16th that he could not, after careful investigation, verify the rumor
                    that Gámez was lending assistance to any movement against Nicaragua, or that he
                    was in constant communication with General Vásquez. He added that in San José
                    there was no evidence of the existence of any activity against Nicaragua.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
